<TEXT>
a sheriff played some mind games to rope 
in drug users headed for a country music fest in the north woods 
and the trick paid off with 20 arrests 
after posting a sign friday that read narcotics inspection 
ahead six officers in camouflage hid by the roadside 
positioning themselves so they could see the reaction of the people 
in passing vehicles on state route 55 
if the cars slowed down and those inside tried to conceal or 
discard something the officers radioed ahead for patrolmen to pull 
them over said langlade county sheriff dave steger 
some open beer cans were tossed out windows but no one threw 
drugs away one officer told a reporter at the scene 
theyre too expensive he said 
most of the arrests were for marijuana possession and a few 
were for cocaine possession and posession with intent to deliver 
he said 
officers accepted 100 bail in the form of personal checks 
credit cards or cash 
soon after the operation began promoters of the weekend country 
music festival at the mole lake indian reservation about 220 miles 
north of milwaukee arrived at the arrest site a few miles south of 
the reservation to find out what was going on 
it didnt take long for the word to spread steger said 
steger said accusations of entrapment did not worry him there 
was good probable cause on all the stops we did make he said 
