<TEXT>
about 250 reformminded lawmakers held a strategy 
meeting today for what promises to become the national parliaments 
first organized opposition in nearly 70 years 
the fledgling faction of soviet legislators operating under the 
bland title of the interregional deputies group is pushing 
for more radical economic reform and greater democracy 
progressive economist gavriil popov opened the groups first 
general meeting in the crowded auditorium of the soviet filmmakers 
union with a call to bring reform through careful legal changes 
instead of the governments spontaneous approach to crisis 
after crisis 
speakers then began discussing amendments and projects they want 
to lobby for in the supreme soviet legislature 
organizers said many more than the 250 deputies who registered 
for the twoday general meeting wanted to come but some could not 
obtain tickets and others were too involved in local events all 
2250 deputies elected to this springs congress of peoples 
deputies were eligible to join 
tass which dubbed the group leftradicals said today they 
have a place in the reform process but that some legislators have 
expressed the fear that in this complex time for the country when 
unity of action is required this leftradical group might turn 
into some kind of opposition 
in fact some members say the group already sees itself as an 
opposition faction but avoids saying so publicly 
were avoiding the words opposition and faction because 
theyre perceived negatively moscow deputy yuri andreyev said in 
an interview but in actuality this is a group of opposition 
deputies who want to work in an organized way at the congress and 
the supreme soviet 
moscow deputy sergei stankevich writing in the first issue of 
the groups newspaper the peoples deputy said that fears 
instilled by years of political tyranny made people shy away from 
the idea of open opposition 
no sooner does someone pronounce the words faction and 
opposition from the rostrum than some people feel their hearts 
drop into their feet and their backs break out in sweat and others 
get a hunters spark in their eyes and a militant shout in their 
throats he wrote 
tass predicted that maverick communist boris n yeltsin would be 
elected head of the interregional group elections were to be held 
on sunday 
thus far the group has been tolerated but given no concrete 
support by the government apparatus and was denied its own meeting 
place in the kremlin organizers said 
it is working on setting up its own staff and support base said 
elena kotova head of the twoweekold foundation of deputies 
initiatives 
the foundation is searching for legal ways for voters to 
contribute money to their deputies and also hopes to act as a data 
bank and channel for voters requests kotova said 
our desired aim is to have the equivalent of a western 
party she said 
the last alternative party to survive the bolshevik purges the 
left socialist revolutionaries was suppressed in 1922 
the interregional group grew out of the despair of the 
radicallyinclined minority during the congress when they found 
virtually all their motions blocked by what one deputy called the 
aggressively obedient majority the newspaper peoples deputy 
said 
popov proposed creation of an independent group of deputies on 
may 27 the third day of the congress the congress lasted two 
weeks it served as a national stage for striking revelations about 
the countrys crises and launched commissions but produced little 
actual legislation 
the congress postponed the resolution of essential problems 
for an undefined period the peoples deputy said and that led 
to strikes and the sharpening of the interethnic situation 
among questions discussed today were amendments that would give 
enterprises more independence from ministries and a resolution 
asking that soviets living abroad who were stripped of their 
citizenship be allowed to reclaim it 
</TEXT>
