<TEXT>
hungary has dismantled nearly half of 
the barbed wire fence and alarm system that has divided this 
communist nation from the west for more than 30 years an official 
said 
balazs novaki deputy commander in chief of the hungarian 
frontier guards told reporters on friday that work on removing 
hungarys iron curtain has progressed more swiftly than planned 
hungarian leaders presented president bush with a piece of the 
barbed wire fence when he visited budapest earlier this month 
speaking at a news conference at the border town of koeszeg 
novaki said the system now has been removed from a 75mile section 
of hungarys 160mile border with neutral austria the official mti 
news agency reported 
during the spring workers began cutting through the barbed wire 
at four stops along the border and officials said then they 
expected to dismantle the barrier completely by dec 1 1990 
hungary decided in february to remove the fence and electronic 
alarm system that was installed in 1972 novaki said restrictions 
in the 15milewide border zone such as on travel and movement 
will be lifted aug 1 but that guards will continue to patrol the 
border 
the number of western tourists visiting hungary has increased 
considerably this year novaki said with the biggest increases 
among visitors from austria west germany the netherlands and the 
united states 
officials also have said there has been a substantial increase 
in the number of citizens from other east bloc countries attempting 
to flee to the west over the hungarian border since they began 
dismantling the fence most are from east germany officials have 
said 
</TEXT>
