in 1970 a worse record than other widebodied airliners 
beyer said the figures are misleading he said 18 dc10s 
actually have been destroyed but only three were due to accidents 
involving mechanical problems 
these include the iowa crash where investigators are trying to 
determine why the planes tail engine blew up destroying hydraulic 
flight controls 
another involved an american airlines dc10 that crashed on 
takeoff from chicago in 1979 becoming what is still the worst us 
aviation disaster in history with 274 people killed the crash was 
blamed on faulty maintenance 
also in 1974 a turkish airlines dc10 crashed over paris 
killing 346 people after a cargo door popped off the cabin 
decompressurized the cargo hold roof buckled and control lines 
were severed 
a court order grounded all dc10s for 37 days after the 1979 
chicago crash and the aircraft was modified for safety after both 
the paris and chicago crashes 
but beyer said 15 other dc10s were destroyed by ground fires 
an aborted takeoff bad landings other pilot errors or birds in an 
engine 
among more recent concerns raised about dc10s is rep john 
dingells suggestion that spare military parts might have been used 
in the engine of the dc10 that crashed in iowa the engine 
builder general electric says this is impossible but the 
michigan democrat asked the federal aviation administration to 
investigate 
