<TEXT>
amoco corp has signed an agreement to explore 
for oil in poland according to a published report 
under the contract signed friday in new york amoco and the 
stateowned polish oil and gas co will conduct a 12month joint 
study of geological and geophysical data on roughly 40 percent of 
the country the chicago tribune reported saturday 
if the exploration indicates potential oil reserves amoco and 
polish oil and gas would negotiate a second contract that would 
enable the chicagobased company to drill exploratory wells and 
ultimately produce oil 
amoco production co employees will go to warsaw next month and 
polish oil and gas employees will eventually come to the us 
production companys houston headquarters to study the data 
amoco the fifthbiggest usbased energy company has been 
conducting a similar study in yugoslavia 
poland produces only 3000 barrels of oil a day according to 
central intelligence agency estimates by comparison illinois 
pumps 63000 barrels a day 
poland consumes an estimated 540000 barrels of oil a day much 
of that obtained from the soviet union in exchange for machinery 
and other goods 
but the potential for oil is indicated by polands abundance of 
coal the two hydrocarbons are often found in proximity to one 
another 
poland hasnt explored intensively for oil for at least 45 
years and thus may have missed deposits detectable with todays 
sophisticated equipment said alfred munk amocos manager of 
foreign affairs 
its a problem of technical capabilities and money said jan 
szczurowski the economic attache at the polish commercial 
consulars office in new york 
