parliament speaker hashemi rafsanjani was 
elected president by a landslide majority according to official 
returns announced saturday 
governmentrun tehran radio reported rafsanjani won 13468355 
out of 14192802 votes cast friday in 192 out of 198 regions or 
about 95 percent 
it also said 97 percent of the voters approved constitutional 
amendments boosting the presidents executive power 
tehran radio said rafsanjanis only opponent parliament deputy 
abass sheibani from the token opposition party the freedom 
movement won 483050 votes or about 3 percent 
sheibani conceded defeat in a letter to rafsanjani read over the 
radio and was quoted as saying i congratulate you on your 
election which was achieved with a definite vote 
irans official media did not say how many of the countrys 25 
million voters age 16 or older turned out to vote or when full 
results would be reported about 17 million people voted in last 
years parliamentary elections 
irans main opposition group the mujahedeen khalq or peoples 
warriors said in a statement released at its headquarters in 
baghdad iraq that turnout was low 
rafsanjani a socalled pragmatist in irans religious 
hierarchy will be the islamic republics fourth president he will 
succeed ayatollah ali khamenei who was chosen supreme leader after 
the death june 3 of ayatollah ruholla khomeini 
rafsanjani is expected to move toward restoring links with the 
west and liberalizing irans economy to help the countrys 
reconstruction after the eightyear iraniraq war which was 
suspended by a ceasefire last august 
the constitutional amendments approved in the election do away 
with the post of prime minister and put the president in charge of 
the government answerable only to the 270seat majlis or 
parliament 
the changes are designed to eliminate competing power centers 
that have for years paralyzed the government and blocked economic 
reforms 
