cicconi 37 runs the white house appointment office 
the newspaper reported that the balloontype loan from first 
american mortgage company was made in september 1984 for an 
original term of 90 days under the arrangement cicconi did not 
have to pay interest which amounted to 10 percent a year or 
principal until the loan expired and in december 1984 first 
american exercised an option clause that extended the loan for an 
additional year 
the mortgage company sought protection under federal bankruptcy 
laws in late 1985 and its owner and other executives later were 
convicted on federal charges of defrauding company investors of 
millions of dollars 
cicconis lawyer william b hundley said cicconi tried on 
several occasions after the extension expired in december 1985 to 
repay the loan and its accumulated interest but hundley said 
cicconi just couldnt get any information at all as to who owned 
the note or where to send the money 
