escape and notified rescue workers 
cuevas said rescue crews and firefighters were on the scene late 
saturday night and that it would probably take 12 hours for them 
to reach the trapped miners 
curanilahue is about 390 miles south of santiago in the heart of 
the chilean coal mining region 
the region is wet most of the year and water continuously leaks 
into the mines which contain large pockets of water cuevas said 
he said it had been raining in the area but that there was no 
reason to believe that the precipitation caused the accident 
the mine is privately owned and all work is under contract for 
the state coal company enacar cuevas said enacars rescue crews 
were on the scene he said 
</TEXT>
