are part of the unrelenting pursuit of good management in 
practice especially when times are comfortable both theory and 
practice fall into disuse 
what awakens both of them is competition and competiton now is 
global rather than regional or national the route to the 
consumers heart isnt is nationality but price and quality 
only the slimmest and trimmest can offer it 
